<file path="reference/legacy-flask-note/DO-NOT-COPY-FLASK.md">
# Do Not Copy Legacy Flask Runtime

The following old prototype parts were intentionally excluded:

- Flask route files
- Jinja templates
- static CSS
- cache files
- user JSON
- secrets
- pycache

Reason:
The target architecture is React + ASP.NET Core + SQL Server + Clean Architecture.
</file>

<file path="reference/README.md">
# Reference Assets

These files come from the old prototype and are kept as business/technical reference only.

## /reference/express
Express DBF extraction logic and sample trial balance data.

## /reference/financial
Financial statement SQL mapping and Python prototype calculation logic.

## /reference/requirements
Original requirement document.

Do not run these as part of the new production system.
Convert the concepts into C# services and SQL Server schema.
</file>

